def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    if isinstance(data, Series):
        level = clocs[0]
        dummy_index = data.unstack(level, fill_value=fill_value).index
    else:
        skip = index.nlevels - len(clocs)
        new_names = index.names[:skip] + (None,)
        
        dummy = data.unstack(clocs[0], fill_value=fill_value)
        new_levels = dummy.columns.levels
        new_codes = dummy.columns.codes
        
        for level in clocs[1:]:
            dummy = dummy.unstack(level, fill_value=fill_value)
            new_levels = new_levels.append(dummy.columns.levels)
            new_codes = new_codes.append(dummy.columns.codes)
        
        new_columns = MultiIndex.from_tuples(dummy.columns, names=new_names)
        
        if isinstance(data.columns, MultiIndex):
            new_columns = new_columns.insert(0, data.columns, insert_loc=skip)
        
        unstacked = DataFrame(np.array(dummy), index=index, columns=new_columns)
    return unstacked
